Mien P., 37, is a low-income woman. She is the leader for a group loan for four other people. Mien P. and her husband currently work at the local fish market, which typically generates an income of $4 a day.  They use their income to pay for food and for school fees for their children. Most of their children go to work with them when they are free from studying. Mien P. says that her income is sufficient  for her family’s requirements but she and her family are facing difficulties with their living conditions due to the bad condition of their house. She therefore applies for a loan to repair her house. The other four borrowers that are jointly taking this loan are:
V., who will be using the loan to decorate her house; 
N., who will use the loan to repair her house; 
P., who requests a loan to increase her grocery inventory for sale; and 
N., who will use her first loan to repair her old house.
